<h2>ESSA – North Dakota School Accountability Dashboard</h2>
<img width="258" height="16" alt="Sidebar Hr" src="http://www.southheart.k12.nd.us/wp-content/themes/Polished/images/sidebar_hr.png" class="divider"><div class="textwidget">North Dakota has a new accountability system for the recently adopted federal law called the “Every Student Succeeds Act (ESSA).”  School performance is now reported through NDInsights, more commonly referred to as the “Dashboard.” The Dashboard replaces the former Adequate Yearly Progress (AYP) reports used with the previous federal law called “No Child Left Behind (NCLB).”  The Dashboard contains reports that display the performance of all North Dakota school districts, including South Heart School.  Click on the following link to access the <a href="https://insights.nd.gov/" target="_blank">North Dakota Dashboard</a>.</div>
